Priming and Message Size Analysis
Purpose
This document analyzes the impact of priming message sizes across all 26 repositories in the Arcadia system and provides the technical justification for optimizing network and Aeron configuration settings.
Recommended Changes
Based on comprehensive analysis of message sizes, fragmentation patterns, and performance characteristics, the following configuration changes are recommended:
1. Priming Page Size (Code Change)
•	Current: pageSize = 5 records per message
•	New: pageSize = 100 records per message
•	Impact: 20x fewer messages, reduces priming time from 1.5-3s to 100-200ms per 1000 auctions
2. Aeron MTU Settings (Docker Configuration)
•	Current: MTU = 1,408 bytes (default)
•	New: MTU = 8,192 bytes (jumbo frames)
•	Settings: 
•	-Daeron.mtu.length=8192
•	-Daeron.ipc.mtu.length=8192
•	Impact: 5.8x fewer fragments per message, 99.3% network efficiency (vs 95.5%)
3. Aeron Socket Buffers (Need SRE help)
•	Current: ~200 KB (OS default)
•	New: 2 MB send/receive buffers
•	Settings: 
•	-Daeron.socket.so_rcvbuf=2097152
•	-Daeron.socket.so_sndbuf=2097152
•	Impact: Prevents buffer congestion, supports messages up to 1 MB safely
4. OS Socket Buffer Limits (System Configuration)
•	Current: net.core.rmem_max = 212,992 bytes (~200 KB)
•	New: net.core.rmem_max = 8,388,608 bytes (8 MB)
•	Required: OS must allow Aeron to request 2 MB buffers
