Performance Impact
Detailed Transmission Time Breakdown
For Auction records (2 KB each), priming 1000 records:
Metric	Before (Page=5, MTU=1408)	After (Page=100, MTU=8192)	Improvement
Message Configuration			
Records per message	5	100	20x
Message size (with header)	10,280 bytes	204,840 bytes	~20x
Messages for 1000 auctions	200	10	20x fewer
Network Fragmentation			
MTU size	1,408 bytes	8,192 bytes	5.8x
Fragments per message	8	25	3.1x
Network overhead per message	480 bytes	1,500 bytes	3.1x
Total on wire per message	10,760 bytes	206,340 bytes	19.2x
Network efficiency	95.5%	99.3%	+3.8%
Transmission Timing			
Pure network transfer	0.086 ms	1.65 ms	19.2x
Fragment assembly time	0.4 ms (8 × 0.05ms)	1.25 ms (25 × 0.05ms)	3.1x
Total per message	0.486 ms ≈ 0.5 ms	2.9 ms	5.8x
Total for 1000 auctions			
Message transmission only	200 × 0.5ms = 100 ms	10 × 2.9ms = 29 ms	3.4x faster
Calculation Details:
Before (Page=5, MTU=1408):
Message size: (5 × 2,048) + 40 = 10,280 bytes
Fragments: 10,280 / 1,408 = 7.3 → 8 fragments
Network overhead: 8 × 60 = 480 bytes
Total on wire: 10,280 + 480 = 10,760 bytes

Transmission @ 1 Gbps: 10,760 bytes / 125,000,000 bytes/s = 0.086 ms
Assembly: 8 fragments × 0.05 ms/fragment = 0.4 ms
Total: 0.086 + 0.4 = 0.486 ms ≈ 0.5 ms per message
After (Page=100, MTU=8192):
Message size: (100 × 2,048) + 40 = 204,840 bytes
Fragments: 204,840 / 8,192 = 25 fragments (exactly)
Network overhead: 25 × 60 = 1,500 bytes
Total on wire: 204,840 + 1,500 = 206,340 bytes

Transmission @ 1 Gbps: 206,340 bytes / 125,000,000 bytes/s = 1.65 ms
Assembly: 25 fragments × 0.05 ms/fragment = 1.25 ms
Total: 1.65 + 1.25 = 2.9 ms per message
Why is each message slower but overall faster?
•	Per-message time: 0.5ms → 2.9ms (5.8x slower per message)
•	Message count: 200 → 10 (20x fewer messages)
•	Net result: 100ms → 29ms (3.4x faster overall)
Key insight: Sending fewer, larger messages is more efficient than many small messages.
 
Real-World Priming Performance
The transmission times above are only part of the story. Actual priming includes:
Before Optimization (Priming Page=5, MTU=1408):
•	Pure transmission: 200 messages × 0.5ms = 100ms
•	Round-trip latency: 200 × 5ms = 1,000ms (request → response cycles)
•	Processing overhead: 200 × 2ms = 400ms (mapping, validation, repository updates)
•	Total observed time: 1.5-3 seconds in practice
After Optimization (Priming Page=100, MTU=8192):
•	Pure transmission: 10 messages × 2.9ms = 29ms
•	Round-trip latency: 10 × 5ms = 50ms (request → response cycles)
•	Processing overhead: 10 × 2ms = 20ms (mapping, validation, repository updates)
•	Total observed time: 100-200ms in practice
Overall Improvement:
Component	Before	After	Improvement
Transmission	100 ms	29 ms	3.4x faster
Round-trip latency	1,000 ms	50 ms	20x faster
Processing	400 ms	20 ms	20x faster
Total	1.5-3s	100-200ms	15-20x faster 🚀
The 20x reduction in message count is the primary driver of improvement, reducing both round-trip overhead and processing time proportionally.
 
